%text If $F$ be the fuel-costs per hour and $T$ the total costs per hour, then % \begin{align}
F \propto s^3 &\implies F = ks^3 \\ &\implies F = \dfrac{6}{25}\cdot s^3 \dph \\ \therefore T &= \left(\dfrac{6}{25}s^3 + 480\right) \dph \end{align} %text
